                        "name": "Instinctual Tinker",
                        "type": "offensive_action",
                        "text": "The morlock tinkers with an adjacent construct or mechanical hazard. They attempt a <a aonid=\"4\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Crafting</a> check against the construct's or hazard's Fortitude DC. The morlock can't succeed if the target's level is more than double the morlock's. <br/><b>Critical Success</b> The target gains 4d6 HP and a +1 circumstance bonus to attack rolls for 1 minute. <br/><b>Success</b> The target gains 2d6 HP. <br/><b>Critical Failure</b> The morlock injures itself, taking 2d6 damage (typically bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing, but potentially a different type at the GM's discretion).",
                        "action": {
